cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper focuses on the problem of semantic segmentation in RGB-D images using a combination of parametric proposals and pooling methods. The paper discusses the use of deep learning and inference algorithms, which are commonly associated with computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of multiple features and spatial partitions, which are also common in machine learning (cs.LG) and robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on a large dataset, which is often associated with multimedia (cs.MM) research.
